1b819562-4fd2-4461-b286-7e7042140d05.title: King Roald
1b819562-4fd2-4461-b286-7e7042140d05.text:
Well hello there. What do you want with the king of
Misthalin?

96da564e-8940-49e6-830d-63806b7a7f73.title: King Roald
96da564e-8940-49e6-830d-63806b7a7f73.text:
Well then I must ask that you move along. I'm very
busy. I am the king after all.

f273d12e-7b99-46a4-a633-c193c7bde78e.title: King Roald
f273d12e-7b99-46a4-a633-c193c7bde78e.text:
A quest you say? Hmm, what an odd request to make
of the king. It's funny you should mention it though, as
there is something you can do for me.

f9eb1d36-a723-473f-bd74-0c886d9e8b7d.title: King Roald
f9eb1d36-a723-473f-bd74-0c886d9e8b7d.text:
Are you aware of Paterdomus? It's a temple east of
here. It stands on the River Salve and guards the only
passage into the deadly lands of Morytania.

0ffdbd74-f390-42f9-88f0-5c87bb86144e.title: <player>
0ffdbd74-f390-42f9-88f0-5c87bb86144e.text: No, I don't think I know it...

a6862bee-82c0-49d5-b211-9395f41d0032.title: King Roald
a6862bee-82c0-49d5-b211-9395f41d0032.text:
Hmm, how strange that you don't. Well anyway, it has
been some days since last I heard from Drezel, the
priest who lives there.

d9de31e1-3ad9-45bc-bb17-829a435e4ec2.title: King Roald
d9de31e1-3ad9-45bc-bb17-829a435e4ec2.text:
Be a sport and go make sure that nothing untoward
has happened to the silly old codger for me, would you?

2c2b7464-40c0-461e-af6d-38ab61963f1b.title: Start the Priest in Peril quest?

80e352f1-34c1-4d85-bfb9-f13025f41f16.title: King Roald
80e352f1-34c1-4d85-bfb9-f13025f41f16.text:
Yes, I dare say it does. I wouldn't even have
mentioned it had you not seemed to be looking for
something to do anyway.

55d38969-83dd-42df-a55e-b1d51a6a64df.title: <player>
55d38969-83dd-42df-a55e-b1d51a6a64df.text: Sure. I don't have anything better to do right now.

c0858167-be83-43f1-9d96-9ea83033dcea.title: King Roald
c0858167-be83-43f1-9d96-9ea83033dcea.text:
Many thanks adventurer! I would have sent one of my
squires but they wanted payment for it!

options.text: Why do you care about Drezel anyway?
Do I get a reward for this?

5577b3b9-047e-462f-8e29-09fd095215c6.title: <player>
5577b3b9-047e-462f-8e29-09fd095215c6.text: Why do you care about Drezel anyway?

b7d21487-4d65-4109-b126-62e1f444bed6.title: King Roald
b7d21487-4d65-4109-b126-62e1f444bed6.text:
Well, that is a slightly impertinent question to ask of
your king, but I shall overlook it this time.

40488345-3020-4bf4-a441-37e9de582022.title: King Roald
40488345-3020-4bf4-a441-37e9de582022.text:
As you are no doubt aware, this kingdom worships
Saradomin, the god of wisdom and order. As such, it is
a peaceful place to live and prosper.

646bc5f0-c419-4e01-9577-2a546d877c33.title: King Roald
646bc5f0-c419-4e01-9577-2a546d877c33.text:
Paterdomus, the temple where Drezel lives, stands on
the eastern border of Misthalin. It guards the only
passage into the evil lands of Morytania.

99a05b93-7c9b-4da6-a1a1-e2648f8cf025.title: King Roald
99a05b93-7c9b-4da6-a1a1-e2648f8cf025.text:
Oh yes. Morytania is a fearful place, filled to the brim
with accursed servants of the chaos god Zamorak. All of
them are terrible, but none more so than the rulers of
the region, the vampyres.

fca371ea-e852-48a1-921a-826c98ad5753.title: King Roald
fca371ea-e852-48a1-921a-826c98ad5753.text:
Thankfully, the sacred River Salve marks a natural
border between Misthalin and Morytania. Together, the
river and the temple prevent any invasion by the
vampyres.

df5a2503-3f3a-4318-9238-8a821e14674d.title: King Roald
df5a2503-3f3a-4318-9238-8a821e14674d.text:
The waters of the river are kept blessed with
Saradomin's almighty power. This ensures our defences
remain strong, as the vampyres cannot cross such a
holy barrier.

4bbc28b1-8eb2-4997-a45d-9a5894f15b7d.title: King Roald
4bbc28b1-8eb2-4997-a45d-9a5894f15b7d.text:
Drezel is descended from one of the original
Saradominist priests who first blessed the river. His job
is to ensure nothing happens to the river that might
allow the evil of Morytania to invade this land.

c843031c-22f3-4f4a-8bdd-ab3bbd9d63f8.title: King Roald
c843031c-22f3-4f4a-8bdd-ab3bbd9d63f8.text:
This is the reason why the lack of communication from
him bothers me somewhat, although I am sure nobody
would dare to try and attack our kingdom!

options.text: Do I get a reward for this?

7ba6e273-ee62-4bc3-928b-f62b12755095.title: <player>
7ba6e273-ee62-4bc3-928b-f62b12755095.text: Do I get a reward for this?

feecbca6-0dbe-4a28-b8cd-8fdbdb6a77f8.title: King Roald
feecbca6-0dbe-4a28-b8cd-8fdbdb6a77f8.text:
You will be rewarded in the knowledge that you have
done the right thing and assisted the king of Misthalin.

80e96cd3-3584-41e7-a356-5b98c6ad6428.title: <player>
80e96cd3-3584-41e7-a356-5b98c6ad6428.text: Soooooo...... that would be a 'no' then?

options.text: Why do you care about Drezel anyway?

f73bfaf1-9de8-4342-9046-660d0ddea863.title: King Roald
f73bfaf1-9de8-4342-9046-660d0ddea863.text:
Drezel is the priest who lives at Paterdomus, the temple
to the east. You're supposed to be making sure that
nothing bad has happened to him. Remember?

c98c600b-2b7b-44fb-a6da-9cc173c7f274.title: <player>
c98c600b-2b7b-44fb-a6da-9cc173c7f274.text: Ooooooooh, THAT Drezel. Yup, I remember.

afd3a528-a563-4fcb-afa1-0d4aa40edc03.title: King Roald
afd3a528-a563-4fcb-afa1-0d4aa40edc03.text: You have news of Drezel for me?

options.text: Where am I supposed to go again?
Why do you care about Drezel anyway?
Do I get a reward for this?

392a4cd6-54ac-4263-881a-6df598026663.title: <player>
392a4cd6-54ac-4263-881a-6df598026663.text: Why do you care about Drezel anyway?

ce0dd449-93cc-48d1-8087-3091d0cd4826.title: King Roald
ce0dd449-93cc-48d1-8087-3091d0cd4826.text:
Well, that is a slightly impertinent question to ask of
your king, but I shall overlook it this time.

abf0bd46-051e-4e00-91a8-efdbed70f2cf.title: King Roald
abf0bd46-051e-4e00-91a8-efdbed70f2cf.text:
As you are no doubt aware, this kingdom worships
Saradomin, the god of wisdom and order. As such, it is
a peaceful place to live and prosper.

1642ff92-87f7-4097-be04-bd96ea0e3379.title: King Roald
1642ff92-87f7-4097-be04-bd96ea0e3379.text:
Paterdomus, the temple where Drezel lives, stands on
the eastern border of Misthalin. It guards the only
passage into the evil lands of Morytania.

6604d341-89c9-4daa-b391-8c9497e3d441.title: King Roald
6604d341-89c9-4daa-b391-8c9497e3d441.text:
Oh yes. Morytania is a fearful place, filled to the brim
with accursed servants of the chaos god Zamorak. All of
them are terrible, but none more so than the rulers of
the region, the vampyres.

cbd328d2-92f6-4131-ab2b-d76ffc5e3b90.text:
Thankfully, the sacred River Salve marks a natural
border between Misthalin and Morytania. Together, the
river and the temple prevent any invasion by the
vampyres.

c01f241a-8208-40a0-bfe5-1882d7a7b9dd.title: King Roald
c01f241a-8208-40a0-bfe5-1882d7a7b9dd.text:
The waters of the river are kept blessed with
Saradomin's almighty power. This ensures our defences
remain strong, as the vampyres cannot cross such a
holy barrier.

1c71b842-8a53-4b41-9034-33353f97e547.title: King Roald
1c71b842-8a53-4b41-9034-33353f97e547.text:
Drezel is descended from one of the original
Saradominist priests who first blessed the river. His job
is to ensure nothing happens to the river that might
allow the evil of Morytania to invade this land.

169cd7d7-3209-4819-9fcc-60e039de8463.title: King Roald
169cd7d7-3209-4819-9fcc-60e039de8463.text:
This is the reason why the lack of communication from
him bothers me somewhat, although I am sure nobody
would dare to try and attack our kingdom!

options.text: Do I get a reward for this?

a519bd36-de84-4cac-8667-bc2d6569dc9e.title: <player>
a519bd36-de84-4cac-8667-bc2d6569dc9e.text: Do I get a reward for this?

9c811230-6ade-4c8a-87a8-41db33f63355.title: King Roald
9c811230-6ade-4c8a-87a8-41db33f63355.text:
You will be rewarded in the knowledge that you have
done the right thing and assisted the king of Misthalin.

91a3d90f-e717-46a3-9e5b-fc86c27b54c1.title: <player>
91a3d90f-e717-46a3-9e5b-fc86c27b54c1.text: Soooooo...... that would be a 'no' then?

options.text: Why do you care about Drezel anyway?

eb10d943-c9b9-4535-8b49-3017c352153d.title: King Roald
eb10d943-c9b9-4535-8b49-3017c352153d.text:
Drezel is the priest who lives at Paterdomus, the temple
to the east. You're supposed to be making sure that
nothing bad has happened to him. Remember?

b9c8cf9a-b2a2-4f38-b7ff-5ee11f54428e.title: <player>
b9c8cf9a-b2a2-4f38-b7ff-5ee11f54428e.text: Ooooooooh, THAT Drezel. Yup, I remember.

16e2548c-5b34-4e66-a02a-32ded26950bb.title: <player>
16e2548c-5b34-4e66-a02a-32ded26950bb.text: Where am I supposed to go again?

b0178426-d43b-435b-85b8-6e1d0727311c.title: King Roald
b0178426-d43b-435b-85b8-6e1d0727311c.text:
The temple of Paterdomus where Drezel lives. It is but
a short journey east from here. It lies south of the
cliffs, at the source of the River Salve.

bb3d868f-809a-47b9-acbe-9723101f19be.title: King Roald
bb3d868f-809a-47b9-acbe-9723101f19be.text: Don't worry, you can't miss it.

options.text: Do I get a reward for this?
Why do you care about Drezel anyway?
Do I get a reward for this?

f920bd64-1280-418f-a6b6-e6c08a5fce20.title: King Roald
f920bd64-1280-418f-a6b6-e6c08a5fce20.text: You have news of Drezel for me?

de859ad9-f4ff-4604-83a1-db17097422b9.title: <player>
de859ad9-f4ff-4604-83a1-db17097422b9.text:
Well... I went to the temple like you asked me to... and
I spoke to someone inside...

44b1b887-e202-4261-b9ec-1551f323d004.title: King Roald
44b1b887-e202-4261-b9ec-1551f323d004.text:
Ah, well that must have been Drezel then. What did he
say?

e5aac541-fdb5-4344-96b4-05a9d37a0dba.title: <player>
e5aac541-fdb5-4344-96b4-05a9d37a0dba.text:
Well... he seemed to be having some kind of trouble. He
asked for my help.

dc876160-a2e2-4dfd-bc98-0884c68feab6.title: King Roald
dc876160-a2e2-4dfd-bc98-0884c68feab6.text:
Well I expect you to offer him your full assistance in
whatever he needs.

f1fd5fb3-226b-4627-af70-38c2a148ca64.title: King Roald
f1fd5fb3-226b-4627-af70-38c2a148ca64.text: You have news of Drezel for me?

c98acc57-b061-4375-84e4-5c85d16840a7.title: <player>
c98acc57-b061-4375-84e4-5c85d16840a7.text:
Yes, I spoke to the guys at the temple. They said they
were being bothered by a dog in the mausoleum, so I
went and killed it for them. No problem.

16b5d7eb-2fc7-4bae-89dc-c65ffc0c1ad8.title: King Roald
16b5d7eb-2fc7-4bae-89dc-c65ffc0c1ad8.text:
That mausoleum contain the only passage between
Morytania and Misthalin! Not only that, it's built right
over the source of the River Salve!

baa48157-88e8-473f-be5a-892e706a609b.title: King Roald
baa48157-88e8-473f-be5a-892e706a609b.text:
YES YOU DID!!!!! Without that 'dog', there's nothing
to stop someone from entering the mausoleum to
sabotage the blessings on the river. Thanks to you, all
of Misthalin is now at risk!

6520c385-9cee-4536-8771-6f6fbd6657f3.title: King Roald
6520c385-9cee-4536-8771-6f6fbd6657f3.text:
No, you absolute cretin! Obviously some fiend has done
something to Drezel and tricked your feeble intellect
into helping them kill that guard dog!

8e83a63e-9fa2-4370-9e00-98e5c08a5fd1.title: King Roald
8e83a63e-9fa2-4370-9e00-98e5c08a5fd1.text:
Now you get back there and do whatever is necessary
to safeguard the kingdom from attack, or I will see you
beheaded for high treason!

017d038f-af3b-4043-a2b3-59f6aa158c60.title: King Roald
017d038f-af3b-4043-a2b3-59f6aa158c60.text: You have news of Drezel for me?

5534e339-fb38-4cca-acec-aade1485d618.title: <player>
5534e339-fb38-4cca-acec-aade1485d618.text:
I do indeed, sire. He has been imprisoned by some
Zamorakian monks.

995b5daf-f0ca-4277-852e-5e615de66829.title: King Roald
995b5daf-f0ca-4277-852e-5e615de66829.text:
What? This is wholly unacceptable! I order you to do
all that you can to free Drezel immediately!

8a391fef-644e-4095-88f0-95e92b65a240.title: King Roald
8a391fef-644e-4095-88f0-95e92b65a240.text: Ah, I see. In that case keep up the good work.

b3907bee-d242-413f-a1e1-d7cd4ad06233.title: <player>
b3907bee-d242-413f-a1e1-d7cd4ad06233.text:
Well, I found the key to his cell and unlocked it, but
there's a vampyre in there stopping him leaving.

f5dded49-0317-40fb-aa5a-122099be1588.title: King Roald
f5dded49-0317-40fb-aa5a-122099be1588.text:
A vampyre? Well, I order you to do something about it
at once!

c32da2b6-047a-458d-9bf7-de4e21b4a321.title: <player>
c32da2b6-047a-458d-9bf7-de4e21b4a321.text: Yeah, I was planning on doing that anyway.

7113301f-1776-45d6-991a-0318666bb5c0.title: King Roald
7113301f-1776-45d6-991a-0318666bb5c0.text:
Good work! Always a place for quick thinkers in my
kingdom!

efaa9465-99e9-42f9-92af-4231bc15cd17.title: King Roald
efaa9465-99e9-42f9-92af-4231bc15cd17.text: Have you ensured Misthalin's border is fully secured?

93cefe9c-2b3d-4c54-b3ec-40489f3755a9.title: <player>
93cefe9c-2b3d-4c54-b3ec-40489f3755a9.text: Not yet. I'm working on it though.

1c0cf2bb-1520-4eb7-b46a-0342b27a08e3.title: King Roald
1c0cf2bb-1520-4eb7-b46a-0342b27a08e3.text: Ah, it's you again. Hello there.

d99a4171-ce16-41d4-ac20-47ef3178dbc1.title: King Roald
d99a4171-ce16-41d4-ac20-47ef3178dbc1.text: Do you have anything of importance to say?

00a38510-8cd7-405c-abdc-eb045c69078f.title: King Roald
00a38510-8cd7-405c-abdc-eb045c69078f.text:
You will have to excuse me, then. I am very busy as I
have a kingdom to run!
